messages.content: Nash wakes up after what is essentially a full rest. Orion is shaking him awake. "Your turn, Nash."
“Right.” He says, yawning. He stares out emptily into the alleyway.
Orion goes to sleep. Nash is alone with their unconscious bodies.

He’s so tired. He just slept for hours, so it’s a ridiculous thing for him to be, objectively, but - he’s so tired. He feels like his entire body’s been dragged through a pit of gravel. He can’t stop thinking about it.

Her on the ground. Unconscious. Near-dead as he, what, kissed her? Because he’s sick? Because he’s insane?

He thinks about Oswalda, too. Her serenity as she explained just how women exercised their power over men, the hand on the reins. He doesn’t want to think about it. When he thinks about it he feels terrified, panicked, the blood in his body thrumming with fear. And that in itself is an admission, isn’t it? That he’s the sort of man that won’t ever be happy or comfortable taking up his rightful position in the world his mothers want to build. *Beneath* them. 

But at the same time, they’re different creatures, right? Ontologically distinct. Like two diametrically opposing magnets. They can’t touch. No synthesis can ever be reached. So even the tension he feels - the push and pull - becomes naturalized, calcified, an inevitable fact of reality. Women exercise their power. Men grapple with that power. Negotiate with it. Grasp at the dangling strings. Whatever leverage they… he can get…

He’s still so scared. He doesn’t understand it, that fear. He doesn’t understand it at all. What are these limp empty bodies *doing* to him? They’re just sleeping. They’re just people… sleeping. Helpless. Quiet. So far away from any demonstrations of anything, of control, of…
He glances at Orion’s form again. Is he… properly sleeping?
He is.
Nash inches closer to him. And just.. examines his face, for a second.

He looks different, when he’s sleeping. His lashes are, like, long. His hair settles against his face. His breaths come out slow and steady, instead of the normal half-panicked neuroticism Nash has come to expect from him.

His face looks soft. But in a different way than Ruth’s? Somehow? He doesn’t understand the difference. But there is one, and it’s important. He knows, somehow, that it’s important.
His hand twitches forwards. An instinctive movement, one that happens without his consent or even awareness. Like it’s natural.
Nash grabs his own wrist. What the fuck is he doing?

His eyes flicker to Orion’s mouth, for a second. Then he covers his face with his hands and, very quietly, screams uncontrollably into his own clasped arms. 

Quietly. Not loudly enough to wake anyone. Obviously.
*What is wrong with you!* *What is wrong with you!* *What is wrong with you!*

*God, was it not enough to… to do that to Ruth in her sleep? Do you have to fall prey to the exact same terrible misstep again?? You won’t GET AWAY with it this time if you try, idiot. There’s no excuse of CPR. There’s no excuse of.. of what she deserves, or what the two of you are owed, or what power she’s brandishing by existing, her hands on the leash that you’re rightfully taking back. This would just be.. it would just be… there wouldn’t be a reason for it! You wouldn’t be upholding anything! Not servitude to a Goddess, not reaffirmation of duty! You’d just be sick! You’d be ffffucking insane! And everyone would know it!!*
*He’s the worst person ever! He might be your only friend, but he’s also the worst person ever! Stop being pathetic! Stop flaying yourself open for someone who doesn’t fucking care!*

He wants it so badly. Holy fuck. He wants it so badly. Just to know. To know what it would be like! To..

He wants to set himself on *fire.* Holy shit. He wants it so badly. Fuck. Fuck. Fuck. This is the worst thing in the entire world. Maybe the worst thing that’s ever happened to anyone? 

He wants to *set himself on fire.*
Nash remains entirely still for the remainder of the shift. He doesn’t look at Orion even once. His face stays fixed on the horizon.
Someone should really put him down.
You start to hallucinate something. At least you must be hallucinating. How else would the duchess be here, appearing before you? She walks towards you with a confident expression.
“What..?” Nash mumbles, confused. “Mo…ther?”
"Good morning, Nash. Are you ready to save the empire?" She smirks.
“Yes.” He says immediately. “Yes, obviously. Are you… really here?”

"Of course, Nash." She bends forward to be face to face with him. "I need you to teach the Hellhounds a bit of a lesson before I can complete my plans, however. Once I leave, get those 2 to head to the abandoned coliseum where Oswalda used to work. Do you know where that is, Nash?"
“Um, no. Where?”
She provides direction. "It’s not accessible normally. But there’s a magically concealed entrance. Just be sure to be stealthy." She provides additional directions for identifying the fake wall.
"Alright." Nash says, nodding. "What will we do there?"
"Kill as many as you can. That traitor Washington will be there too."
Nash swallows. Nods. "Alright."
He pauses for a second.
"How do I... I mean, what should I say to them?" He gestures to Orion and Ruth.
"Whatever you say, do it quick. You’ll miss your window, otherwise." She pats him on the head condescendingly.
"Mom, I..." He struggles for the correct words. "Did you hear about what happened? Back home?"
"To some degree. Why?"
"I just." He swallows again, almost compulsively. "Wanted to let you know. That everyone is okay. That I protected them."
"Good job. Are you asking for some kind of reward?" She seems amused.
"No! I mean, I would never demand anything of you, mother. I just. Wanted to make sure you, knew..." He looks down, shamed.
*Reward me. Reward me, please. Tell me I've done good.*
"You won’t get anything without asking for it, Nash." She starts to leave.
"Wait!"
He calls out.
"Hm?"
"I. I do want a reward, actually. I protected everyone, and maintained your.. the family's dignity."
"Hm? And what is it?"
He pauses. "Whatever you see fit to give me...?"
She approaches him slowly with a cold expression.
He waits.
She kisses Nash’s forehead. "That’s the reward for pleasing the duchess. Though usually I don’t do it like a mother. You can consider that special to you, if you want."
Nash nods, throat suddenly dry. "Th-thank you."
She walks away silently.

Nash just sits for a second, clutching his knees to his chest. He allows himself a second of it - that dizzying fear, comorbid with joy. Acknowledgment. *So why are you scared? So whyyyyy are you scared?*
He doesn't know. He doesn't.. he doesn't know.
In lieu of interrogating himself any further, he instead leans over and shakes Orion awake.
"Huh…? Is it morning?" Orion.
"Listen. I need you to help me convince Ruth of something."
"What? She’s not gonna kiss you again, dude."
"What? N-no! That's not what I'm talking about!"
"Then what?"
"We've got to go to - a place. The abandoned colosseum where my mom used to work. It's an order from my mother."
"What? Why? How would she even-?"
"It's an order! We need to do it, to help - solidify her position. Weed out traitors. It'll keep us safe."
"Uh… Okay, sure. So what do you need my help for?"
"Killing the people there? Obviously."
"I meant with Ruth."
"I figure, if we present a united front, she won't immediately yell no and that we're stupid?"
"I kind of doubt that but okay." He shakes Ruth awake.
Nash waits for her to wake up.

"What?" Ruth.

"Uh, we need to go somewhere." Orion.
"The old colosseum." He says impatiently.

"Why there?" Ruth.

"Uh, you’ll see when we get there?" Orion.
"Yeah."

"Uh, do you know how to get there Nash?" Orion.

"Fine. Just make sure to be stealthy right now. We don’t want guards to notice us." Ruth.
"Yes. My mother told me."
He leads them there.
Stealthily.
((Roll stealth))
They stealth off towards the coliseum. ((End session))
You reach the abandoned coliseum, still hidden. The front entrance has been covered in rubble, but Nash knows where to go to actually get in.
Nash looks for the fake wall. ((Should I roll))

((Nah, the Duchess told you where it is))

You step through the illusion and find several men guarding the passage. Thankfully, they don't seem to notice you.
*Kill as many as you can.*
Nash kills as many as he can. Easy as... that.
((Roll initiative))

The guard on the left does nothing.

It's Nash's turn.
Nash stabs him to death.
((Roll to hit))
It hits.
Does he die?
((That depends on your damage))
((le sighhh is there any sneak attack bonus or anything))
((ok ig not))
((5 for dmg))

He's alive, and your stealth has ended. "Ugh! There's an intruder!"

Ruth misses 2 non-lethal attacks. "What are you doing, Nash!? I thought we were sneaking!"

The guard on the right swings a sword at you and misses.

Orion kills the first guard with an arrow.

It's Nash's turn again.
"We're killing everyone here."
He stabs the guard on the right.
((12 to hit))

It misses. Somehow, everyone in the room misses until it's Nash again. Yes I did roll all of these.

"We are not indiscriminately killing these random people!" Ruth.
"Yes, we are. On her orders."
He tries to stab the guard on the right again.
((19 to hit))
It hits.
((4 for damage))

Ruth punches him, almost knocking him out.

He successfully stabs Nash for 2 damage.

Orion's arrow misses.

It's back to Nash.
Nash tries to stab him. Again.

It misses.

Ruth misses her punches.

He misses his attack on you.

Orion finally kills him with an arrow. 

((End initiative))
Nash sighs, wiping the sweat that's collected on his forehead briefly. "Right. Onwards, then."

"You have to explain yourself, Nash." Ruth.

There's a singular door ahead and no other way to head further in.
"Explain what?" Nash scoffs. "I was given orders from my mother. I'm following them."

"She’s not the boss of us." Ruth.

The ground shakes at a loud explosion. 

"We can fight about this later, guys! Something is obviously going on!" Orion runs through the door.
Nash follows.

You arrive at a long circular hallway with various staircases going up and doors going all around. Selle, Erik, and an unfamiliar woman are fighting more guards in front of the front entrance to the building, which has now been blown open.
Can they see us?
Only if you choose to approach them.

Nash pauses and thinks for a minute. If those two are dealing with the guards in front, then they can sneak in and deal with whomever's inside before returning to get the jump on them and take them out also.
He makes a complicated gesture towards Ruth and Orion that he hopes conveys this sentiment.
((Stealth again? You got 50xp for that fight btw))
((yeah stealth))
((Roll for that then))
Are you headed for the doors, the stairs, or just further down the passage?
Whichever will lead them furthest away from the fight, he guesses.
So the passage, I suppose. The passage just sort of loops around in a circle. What few guards were around in the hallway seem to have been reduced to around 0.
Uh, alright. Maybe up the stairs, then?
((Wait I forgot to include this in the original description)) There is additionally a singular staircase going down. Are you still going up?
We'll go down. What the hell, sure.
They reach an underground dungeon with a few cells. With the exception of 1 empty cell, the others contain unfamiliar civilians. There's a guard watching them.
Nash goes to attack and kill the guard, he fucking guesses.
((Roll))
((13 for initiative))
((I meant roll to hit))

Your attack misses.

"Damn it! Someone broke in!" The guard tries to run upstairs, but is tripped by Ruth, causing him to stumble down the stairs and lose consciousness.
Nash looks to the people in the cells. Who the hell are they?
Just random people, seemingly.
"Who the hell are you?"

"They kidnapped us to motivate the fighters to fight the devil after they mocked him..." One of them.

"He's here, then?" Ruth opens the doors to their cells.
"Fucking cultists."

"Nash, they mean The Devil of Soltaria. Not an actual devil." Orion whispers helpfully.

"Where is he? We need to report this to the empire." Ruth.

"He's in the arena, probably. We don't know beyond that." One of them.
"They're still basically cultists. Shut the fuck up, Orion."

"You shut up, dude." Orion.

"Come on. Let's get these prisoners out." Ruth rushes up the stairs with them.

The unconscious guard remains on the floor, alive.
Nash follows.

They arrive back on the first floor, when a prisoner drops dead from a knife in them. Frank Linjamin appears in front of you. "Whoops! Looks like I missed quite a fun prison break."

Ruth adopts a fighting stance. 

So does Orion. "Shit... I don't think we can take this one, guys."
"Says who???"

"Logic, dude!" Orion.

"Let us begin, fools!" Linjamin lunges at Nash, but he's thrown off-balance as a giant magically imbued mace strikes him directly in the head.

Harriet Dana Edwardson approaches, shining with magical energy. 

The random prisoners rush towards the exit freely.
"What the hell are *you* doing here?" Nash yelps.

"Mom sent me to help you. Usually, I couldn't... But these people killed the emperor. I have to." Harriet.

"Well, at least we've got the edge now." Ruth.

"You... You bitch! How dare you strike me!" Linjamin snarls, getting back up. He doesn't notice the growing cracks on his mask.
"I - help me? What, does she think I can't- that I need your assistance in this matter?" He bites out, face an ugly puce. "Like I'm a child being babysat?"

"Nash, focus on the fight!" Ruth.

Harriet doesn't answer, simply readying herself for another attack.
"Whatever!" Nash howls. "I don't care! I don't care! Congrats on being *acknowledged* by her, aha, ahaha..." Whatever that means.
He tries to stab Linjamin.

"Don't make a mockery of me, Edwardson!" Linjamin tries to stab you back at the same time. Unfortunately for his attack, he freezes in place as he feels his mask break to pieces and fall apart. The face of the faceless is unprotected. He's panicking.

He's not the only one shocked, though. Orion is the first to speak. "Uh... Nash? Why does he look so much like you?"
((sorry about the delay juggling two things at once is hard))
((Is this guy actually supposed to look like Nash or is Orion crazy))
((because he does not To Me but it's picrew so))
((He does. I did my best))

Nash blinks, staggering away for a minute. "What...? What the fuck? Who are you, what are you doing, why are you... why are you..." His voice trails off. Sudden, horrible fear rises in his chest. This man is - he's a foreigner, right? He must be, a, a...

He dashes up the stairs.

"After him!" Ruth runs.

Nash follows. He can't think. There's nothing inside him. He's just following orders because it's the knee-jerk reaction to hearing them, like a dead bug twitching because it hasn't figured out that it's not alive yet. Aha.

The second floor looks similar to the first, with similarly positioned doors and staircases going up or down, but there are several notable door with titles above them. You can also hear loud cheering from the floor above.

Linjamin rushes to the top with his name on it.
Nash follows.

Linjamin breaks a trophy case containing masks and puts one on. "You’re going to pay for that!"
((End session))
Selle wakes up the next morning. The other 2 are already awake.

*...Shit, I was really out for that long.*
Selle gets up, and wipes their eyes hurriedly, and their head spins a bit from getting up too fast.
"...Always getting up last at the worst times. Ugh."
Selle holds their hand to their face.
"Are you ready?" Erik smiles.

"You know what, sure, whatever, I'm ready."
*I just woke up!*

Erik summons a translucent cube around the card in Laura's hand. "The explosion won't leave there, no matter what." 

"Are you *sure*?" Laura.

*The card. This is good, actually.*
"Seems like this is our only option. Are we sure we don't wanna do this outside of the office?"

"Good point, actually. We need to go somewhere with a good view of the city." Erik.

"What? Why?" Laura.

"Because when that card leaves, it's rushing straight to Donald Jameson." Erik.
"That's smart. Let's go."
They exit the catacombs together. ((Roll investigation to find an optimal building))
(nat 20)

Selle leads the group to an accessible and tall building perfectly in the middle of town.

"When you're ready, turn the card over. Yule, make sure you follow the card. At least one of us needs to identify where it ends up, or this is for nothing." Erik.

*Gotta get myself ready.*
Selle nods in accordance, then brushes themselves off and readies themself.

Laura flips the card over, revealing... The 0 of Bombs. Nothing happens.

"I hate these stupid card sets so much." Erik.

The card goes flying away.

((Roll perception))

You've got a good look at it. Erik jumps after it. 

"Wh- Are we supposed to follow him?" Laura.

"But of course. I'm going."
Selle jumps after the card also, trying to follow it as best as they can, giving Laura a thumbs up before going.
((Roll athletics or acrobatics))

The 3 of you hop over building after building, arriving at the remains of the abandoned coliseum. The front door has been reduced to a pile of rubble and cannot be traversed through, but the card simply flies through the cracks between the broken bricks and disappears.
"As I thought. Couldn't be a more suspicious place."

"The question is now, how do we get in?" Erik.

"Donald went in somehow. We've just gotta look around." Laura starts investigating.
((Juni?))
((hi sorry i was caught up in something

*A colosseum, huh. This doesn't bode well.*
"I agree, let's have a good look before trying anything."
Selle joins Laura in trying to investigate the surroundings.
((Roll investigation))

Selle cannot figure this out. Neither can Laura.

"Damn it... How did he get in?" Laura.
"I guess he... Climbed? Teleported?"
"There's a few options. But at the end of the day, it doesn't matter." Erik casts fireball and blows the rubble out of the way of the entrance. The ground itself shakes slightly at this.
"I, uh, considered doing that but you know, trying to be inconscpicuous. Whatever, let's just go."

Erik and Laura rush in.

The new opening leads to a long circular hallway with various staircases going up and doors going all around. 3 guards who seem to be members of the Jameson family turn to you. ((Roll initiative))

Laura pounces on one and stabs him.

A guard tries to hit you with his sword, but misses.

Erik effortlessly disposes of a guard.

It's your turn.

"Take this!"
Selle casts Ice Knife, aiming to hit a guard and make the follow up explosion hit another guard nearby.
(19 accuracy, 2 damage)
((Are you aiming for the one Laura attacked or the unhurt one))
(unhurt)
It hits. Neither one makes the save.
(5 damage to both)

The unhurt one topples over and dies, losing his turn.

Laura finishes off the other guy. Seemingly no one else is in the hallway. 

"Where is everyone?" Erik.
"Hiding in ambush, I guess? Let's be cautious."

((150xp)) Erik opens a door. It looks like sleeping quarters, but no one is inside. "Guess going 1 door at a time is the fastest way. Let's just hope he isn't hiding." 

Laura does the same.
Selle looks around, then follows.
((Roll investigation))

You only find normal side rooms, nothing helpful. 

"There's too many doors down here. Let's just go up." Laura.
Selle nods to agree.

Erik sighs and heads up. The second floor looks similar to the first, with similarly positioned doors and staircases going up or down, but there are several notable door with titles above them. You can also hear loud cheering from the floor above.

"What's all that noise... cheering? Is that in the colosseum?"
Selle looks around and tries to read the titles above the doors.
Each has the name of a leader of the Hellhounds. Locruz and Frank's doors are open currently.

*Ahh shit. I think we might just be fucked here.*
Selle freezes up a bit, then sighs a big sigh.

Laura heads for Donald's door and swings it open. Donald has a remarkably fancy office, you can see metaphorical hundreds of gp in every fiber of the room's furnishings. Unfortunately, he is not in it right now.

"Yeah, no wonder. I think he's gonna have to be up there"
Selle points up.

"Wanna check with Locruz? He's your friend, usually. Maybe you can convince him. Plus, he owes you for saving him." Laura.

"The younger kid?" Erik.

"...Locruz. I don't know about that. He definitely has more loyalty to the Hellhounds than to me, and I doubt he would give up any information. It's best to go ahead with the assumption that nobody here will help us."
Selle thinks a bit.
"Well, we can still give it a shot."
Laura heads to the Locruz door, which happens to contain Aeolian Burr and this woman talking to Locruz.
You wake up the next morning in a cell of some kind with Aliza. One of Jameson's men is guarding the cell door.
“Aaagh.” I stand up.
"Ally? Are you okay?" Aliza.
“…Yeah. I’m fine. You?”
"Yeah. What happened? I just sort of... Passed out." Aliza.
“Some powerful magic, I suppose.”
"Have you seen my dad?"
“Not since our last encounter, no.” I place a hand on one of the bars. “Excuse me, sir, I believe there’s been some kind of misunderstanding.”
"What?" Guard.
I cast charm person. “There’s not actually any need or reason to detain us. We’ve violated no principle or law, nor have we shown any aggression to your group.”
((it's not letting me check your sheet what's your spell dc))
((13 i think?))
He's charmed. "Oh, sorry." He opens the cell door.
“Thank you. Have a nice day.” I just sort of leave.
Aliza follows. The dungeon has a few more cells, but you don't recognize anyone inside of them.
“A privately owned prison… what a horrifying concept.”
"I don't think this counts as a real prison, Ally." Aliza heads towards the stairs leading out of here.
I also head there. “It’s real enough to the people here, surely.”

You arrive at a long hallway that seems to stretch circularly around the whole arena. There are other staircases leading up to higher floors or other doors presumably to various rooms. There's a shockingly small amount of guards walking around. They have not looked at the staircase you're on yet.
“Hm. Could we just slip past them…? I don’t know if there’s anywhere worthwhile to head other than simply ‘out of here’.”
"We have to find my father! And you probably want to find Theo too, no?" Aliza attempts stealth.
“Oh right yeah.” I let her go first and then also attempt to skulk around unnoticed.
((Roll stealth))

You are not hidden at all. A guard immediately notices you as you try to sneak. 

"Okay, let's run, Ally!" Aliza dashes to the closest staircase.
I run, yeah.

The ground shakes as you rush to the stairs. The second floor looks similar to the first, with similarly positioned doors and staircases going up or down, but there are several notable door with titles above them. You can also hear loud cheering from the floor above.
I keep running.
In which direction?
I dunno, upstairs?

The third floor gives access to the coliseum's seats. The entire crowd is filled with cheering members of all of the Hellhound subsidiaries. In the arena itself, The Devil of Soltaria aka The Endless Eclipse battles powerful looking challengers. Despite their clear power, the Eclipse is easily toying with them like prey.
“Ah, of course.” I say this.
"Shh... We can't let them notice us, that's way too many people. Let's go back down." Aliza whispers.
I nod, retreating to the lower floor.
The second floor remains empty. Aliza checks the the name over nearest fancy door, one titled Frank Linjamin of the Faceless.
“…I don’t know if that’s a good idea.” I see if I can hear anyone in that room.
You cannot.
Ok. I check if the door’s locked.

It opens into an oddly normal looking office. The only odd detail is the trophy stand containing a few masks.

"I guess my dad isn't here." Aliza.
“Mm.” I contemplate taking one of the masks and then don’t. Instead I exit the room.

She checks the next door, Locruz Klezmer of Destiny. She opens the door, and this time the titular man is inside. His office is a mess and doesn't really seem to contain anything but accumulating junk.

"You two? What are you doing out!?" Locruz.
“I just left. Hello.”

"You're Locruz... Right?" Aliza.

"Does this look like the time for introductions, moron!? If you broke free, then get out of here! Why are you poking the bear!?" Locruz tries to look tough, but he's clearly nervous.
“Probably wise. But she’s concerned about her father, still.”

"You don't want to know what I'll do to you to get to my father, kid." Aliza attempts intimidation. It works well enough.

"Look, he's fine! I don't know all the details but the Queen still wants to use him." Locruz.
“Oh, well that sounds like everything’s perfectly okay then.” I say this in a bizarre voice that is sarcastic because it obviously isn’t but also wishing Aliza would believe that anyway.

"Bullshit! Where is he?" Aliza.

"You don't want to know! Look- He's with the Queen. If she sees you're free, she'll fucking kill you! She doesn't mess around! The only person she's scared of is the devil." Locruz.
“Oh, we just saw him a second ago.”

"Yes, he's doing a big fight right now. Apparently he's captured some monster he wants to kill in a big show." Locruz.

"A... Monster?" Aliza.
“I feel like the other guy(s) we saw in the arena weren’t quite that. Are they just stalling for time?”
"Well... It's an opening act. You need to rile a crowd up, I guess." Locruz.
“Mm. I see.”
These 2 walk into the room, along with "Selle". They're armed.

"?!?!?!?!??!?!!"
Selle is a bit confused at the sight of 'normal' people being here.
“Oh thats Selle.” Aeolian recognizes patterns.

"Uh... Who's that? I don't know anyone called that."
*Shit, he recognises me through a disguise that made me look distinctly different from like, a week ago?*

"Fuck... Yule, what are you doing here!? How did you find this place? Did you free the prisoners!?" Locruz is panicking.

The blond woman looks at the one with the weird glasses. "Aren't you... The Craig daughter?"

With a dryly smug expression, the woman in question responds. "No, that's my sister."

"Look, everyone shut up. We're here for revenge on Donald Jameson and to find the beast he kidnapped. Are you 2 going to fight us or get out of the way?" Foreign man.
“Are we in the way?”
"Calm down. We haven't done shit yet except fight some guards. We just came to talk to Locruz."

"We want his help, don't we? Best to be honest." Craig.

"Help you!?" Locruz.

The foreign man holds a sword to Locruz's neck. "This place is clearly about to fall apart, now that I've busted the door open. You owe us for that temple rescue. If you don't want loose ends calling you a rat, you'd better work with us to resolve this." 

"Hey, he's just a kid! Don't threaten him with murder!" Blond woman.

Locruz gives her a baffled look on top of his clear fear.
"I told you to calm down. We just need to know where Donald is."
“Most of these seem to be Donald’s men. The man himself, though… I couldn’t say.”

"Look, I... I can tell Destiny to get out of the way. Fine. I'll help you. If things are going this far sideways, the Queen should have cleared out anyway." Locruz is sweating. "...Hopefully. I think Donald's handling the beast in the cages. The way there is kind of confusing, you should head up to the arena and just wait. And... Your father should be hiding out in The Queen's office." He looks at the blond woman. 

"Great, 2 birds with 1 stone." Foreign man.

"Can you 2 help us, then? I'm Aliza Hamill. If we're both against the hellhounds and you have to wait a bit, maybe we can work together?" The blond woman.

"Thank you, Locruz."
Selle, or "Yule", turns to Aliza Hamill.
"Honestly, the more help we can get the better. From experience, the Hellhounds are, something else. The name is Yule. Ignore Aeolian's comment earlier, I have no association with anyone named that."
Selle gives an uneasy side-eye to Aeolian.
“But then how do you know I’m Aeolian though.” Hah. “Never mind.”

"Erik Mussa. I'm from Meleke." Foreign man. You don't recognize that country's name offhand.

"Laura Craig. Underworld Fixer Extraordinaire." Weird glasses.

Locruz sighs and leaves the room.
Selle keeps looking at Aeolian in a way that's saying 'Don't say another word.'
“I’m Aeolian Burr.” I say three words.
I guess I leave this room.
The others follow.
Selle also follows.
Locruz heads to a door reading Lydia Skylar, The Queen Of The Night. "Here you go."

Selle goes to open the door to the office.
"Scariest person's office, huh."
“What. Why are we doing this.”
"What, didn't you need to go in here?"
“Wait, never mind.” I didn’t say that and I didn’t forget what just happened in the preceding conversation. “Proceed.”

Aliza swings the door open.

The Queen is not in here. Instead, these 2 men are playing chess together at a chess table. In fact, there's nothing in this room beyond these 2 playing chess. The older blond man is winning easily.
